  "texts": [
    "When r ≈ r P, then the filter bubble is in fact quite similar to the complete network and includes a large fraction of all users.",
    "But as r declines further, the filter bubble gets smaller and more extreme, and in the limit, it includes a tiny and very extremist fraction of the population.",
    "What this implies, in particular, is that for sufficiently low r, moderate voters are not part of the filter bubble.",
    "This result, which is new relative to Acemoglu, Ozdaglar, and Siderius (2024), and is proved in the Appendix.",
    "Once agents receive articles (regardless of the sharing network P), they update their priors b i according to Bayes' rule to form posterior beliefs bi about θ depending on the message of the article they observe."
  ],
